@startuml
title BidMart core-be – Component Diagram\nCatalog Module (Saffana Firsta Aqila)\nC4 Level 3 expansion of the core-be container
top to bottom direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "core-fe\n(Buyer & Seller UI)" as CoreFE <<Container>>
actor "admin-be\n(internal API caller)" as AdminBE <<Container>>
component "auth-be\nJWT validation" as AuthBE <<Container>>
database "core-db\n[PostgreSQL]\nlistings, listing_images,\ncategories" as CoreDB <<Container>>

package "core-be  [Container: Rust + Axum + Tokio]" {

  package "Catalog Module  src/modules/catalog/" {

    package "Infrastructure Layer" {
      component "AppState\n+ create_router(state)\nDependency Injection root" as AppState <<DI>>

      component "Auth Middleware\nrequire_auth\n→ AuthUser { id, name }" as AuthMW <<Middleware>>

      component "seller_controller\nPOST  /api/v1/seller/listings\nGET   /api/v1/seller/listings\nGET   /api/v1/seller/listings/:id\nPATCH /api/v1/seller/listings/:id\nDELETE /api/v1/seller/listings/:id" as SellerCtrl <<Controller>>

      component "buyer_controller\nGET /api/v1/catalog\nGET /api/v1/catalog/c/:slug\nGET /api/v1/listings/:id" as BuyerCtrl <<Controller>>

      component "category_controller\nGET /api/v1/categories\nGET /api/v1/categories/:id" as CategoryCtrl <<Controller>>

      component "internal_controller\nGET   /internal/listings/:id/status\nPATCH /internal/listings/:id/status\nPATCH /internal/listings/:id/auction\nPATCH /internal/listings/:id/ends-at" as InternalCtrl <<Controller>>

      component "ListingIntegration\nService" as IntService <<Service>>

      component "PostgresListing\nRepository" as PgListingRepo <<Repository>>
      component "PostgresCategory\nRepository\n(recursive CTE for subtree)" as PgCategoryRepo <<Repository>>
      component "PostgresListing\nImageRepository" as PgImageRepo <<Repository>>
      component "PostgresListing\nIntegrationRepository" as PgIntRepo <<Repository>>
    }

    package "Application Layer" {
      component "ListingUseCases\n(seller-side CRUD)\n- create_listing\n- list_my_listings\n- get_my_listing\n- update_listing\n- cancel_listing" as ListingUC <<UseCase>>

      component "BuyerListingUseCases\n(buyer-side read)\n- browse_catalog\n- get_public_listing\n- browse_by_category_slug" as BuyerUC <<UseCase>>

      component "CategoryUseCases\n- list_categories\n- get_category_by_id\n- get_category_by_slug" as CategoryUC <<UseCase>>

      component "DTOs\nCreate/UpdateListingRequest\nListingResponse, ListingDetailResponse\nBuyerListingResponse\nPublicListingQueryParams\nPaginatedResponse<T>" as DTOs <<DTO>>
    }

    package "Domain Layer (pure Rust, no I/O)" {
      component "Entities\nListing, ListingImage, Category\nenum ListingStatus" as Entities <<Entity>>

      component "Ports / Traits\nListingRepository\nCategoryRepository\nListingImageRepository\nListingIntegrationPort" as Ports <<Port>>

      component "Errors\nListingError, CategoryError\n(impl IntoResponse → HTTP status)" as Errors <<Error>>
    }
  }

  package "Other Modules\n(not Saffana's scope)" {
    component "bidding module" as BiddingMod <<Module>>
    component "wallet module" as WalletMod <<Module>>
    component "order module" as OrderMod <<Module>>
  }
}

CoreFE --> SellerCtrl : REST + JWT
CoreFE --> BuyerCtrl : REST (public)
CoreFE --> CategoryCtrl : REST (public)
AdminBE --> InternalCtrl : REST internal

SellerCtrl --> AuthMW : layer
AuthMW --> AuthBE : POST /api/v1/auth/validate\n(JWT verification)

AppState ..> ListingUC : owns Arc
AppState ..> BuyerUC : owns Arc
AppState ..> CategoryUC : owns Arc
AppState ..> IntService : owns Arc

SellerCtrl --> ListingUC : State<AppState>
BuyerCtrl --> BuyerUC : State<AppState>
CategoryCtrl --> CategoryUC : State<AppState>
InternalCtrl --> IntService : State<AppState>

ListingUC ..> Ports : depends on traits\n(Arc<dyn ListingRepository>,\nArc<dyn CategoryRepository>,\nArc<dyn ListingImageRepository>)
BuyerUC ..> Ports : depends on traits
CategoryUC ..> Ports : depends on CategoryRepository
IntService .up.> Ports : implements\nListingIntegrationPort

ListingUC --> DTOs : produces / consumes
BuyerUC --> DTOs : produces / consumes
CategoryUC --> DTOs : produces / consumes

ListingUC ..> Entities : uses
ListingUC ..> Errors : returns

PgListingRepo .up.> Ports : implements\nListingRepository
PgCategoryRepo .up.> Ports : implements\nCategoryRepository
PgImageRepo .up.> Ports : implements\nListingImageRepository
PgIntRepo .up.> Ports : backs\nListingIntegrationPort
IntService --> PgIntRepo : delegates

PgListingRepo --> CoreDB : SQL (listings)
PgCategoryRepo --> CoreDB : SQL (categories,\nrecursive CTE)
PgImageRepo --> CoreDB : SQL (listing_images,\nin transaction)
PgIntRepo --> CoreDB : SQL (listings status,\nauction_id, ends_at)

BiddingMod --> InternalCtrl : link_auction,\nupdate_ends_at,\nupdate_status
OrderMod --> InternalCtrl : update_status (SOLD)

note bottom of Ports
  Hexagonal Architecture:
  domain defines the interfaces (ports),
  infrastructure provides the adapters.
  Use cases never import sqlx / axum.
end note

note bottom of AppState
  AppState::new(pool) wires concrete
  Postgres repositories into the trait
  objects required by every UseCase.
  This is the single composition root.
end note
@enduml
